      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:4:3:2",
      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) إِنِّي أَسْتَعِيرُ كَلْبَ الْمَجُوسِيِّ فَأَصِيدُ بِهِ فَقَالَ ( عليه السلام ) لَا تَأْكُلْ مِنْ صَيْدِهِ إِلَّا أَنْ يَكُونَ عَلَّمَهُ مُسْلِمٌ فَتَعَلَّمَهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Mansour Bin Yunus, from Abdul Rahman Bin Sayaba who said, ",
          "‘I said to Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, ‘I borrowed a dog of the Magians, so I hunted with it. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Do not eat from its prey, except if a Muslims trains it, so it learns it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn al-Hakam from Mansur ibn Yunus from ‘Abd al- Rahman ibn Siyabah who has said the following: “I once asked abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about my borrowing the dog of a Zoroastrian person for hunting. He (the Imam) said, ‘Do not use it for food unless a Muslim has trained it and it has learned.’” "
        ]
      }
